        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You never really had a home or hope, you drifted, and eventually you found yourself.  Not a home, but who you wanted to be.  You were a geek, picked on in school a lot, you retreated into fantasy, always imagining that you wer a warrior, a beserker, a fighter of anyone who came. When High School rolled around you decided to work out, not for anythign, but for you, you wanted to be like Conan, like the Hulk.  You started to really get serious about who you were going to be when you were at JC and took a religions class, it covered Pantheism and the Norse and it just clicked.  Next thing you know you were tatted, braided, blond, and wore an axe around the house.  You sacrificed, you prayed, you live it.  The hope that you could be a Viking in truth was who you were going to be, even if no one else would accept what you made your reality.  Then she came, and you finally found a home."
